1
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:34,708
Professor Ahn is coming soon.

2
00:00:34,708 --> 00:00:37,071
I heard no one applied for the audition.

3
00:00:38,820 --> 00:00:42,223
Then of course the audition will be canceled.

4
00:00:49,832 --> 00:00:52,333
What's going on?
You could have just call.

5
00:00:52,333 --> 00:00:57,333
Lak, I heard
you're boycotting Yoo Jin's audition.

6
00:00:57,333 --> 00:00:59,535
Don't blame Lak.

7
00:00:59,535 --> 00:01:02,041
All of us decided on it together.

8
00:01:02,041 --> 00:01:04,066
Why would we become the sidekick of A?

9
00:01:04,066 --> 00:01:07,541
No! It could be the last chance given to us.

10
00:01:07,541 --> 00:01:09,166
If he was going to give us a chance,

11
00:01:09,166 --> 00:01:11,517
he wouldn't have left us
knowing that we'd dissolve.

12
00:01:19,159 --> 00:01:20,693
But...

13
00:01:21,561 --> 00:01:23,596
It was Yoo Jin Sunbae.

14
00:01:24,420 --> 00:01:25,208
What do you mean?

15
00:01:25,208 --> 00:01:29,999
When Milch abandoned us,
the first person who ran over to see us.

16
00:01:29,999 --> 00:01:32,667
And when we had the Mambo performance

17
00:01:32,667 --> 00:01:35,908
he came right over after getting the text
about the conductor's disappearance.

18
00:01:37,141 --> 00:01:38,441
Really?

19
00:02:07,713 --> 00:02:12,284
No one is coming to audition?

20
00:02:15,327 --> 00:02:16,627
Yes.

21
00:02:19,031 --> 00:02:20,466
What the heck.

22
00:02:21,914 --> 00:02:27,319
I thought they'd believe in me
after all the time we spent together.

23
00:02:38,995 --> 00:02:42,599
No one really came?

24
00:02:46,127 --> 00:02:47,999
Why don't we wait a little longer?

25
00:02:47,999 --> 00:02:50,316
If they were going to come,
they'd have came long ago.

26
00:02:50,316 --> 00:02:52,919
How can judges wait for students?

27
00:02:55,406 --> 00:02:58,791
Professors, should we start now?
It's almost time.

28
00:02:58,791 --> 00:03:02,662
- Start what?
- The audition. Everyone's on standby.

29
00:03:06,599 --> 00:03:09,035
Should we believe in Cha Yoo Jin?

30
00:03:09,035 --> 00:03:11,037
He said he believed in us.

31
00:03:11,037 --> 00:03:14,440
When I think about who believed in us...

32
00:03:14,440 --> 00:03:17,210
Sorry. I'm going first.

33
00:03:23,983 --> 00:03:27,120
Did you see the text? Lak, that traitor...

34
00:03:27,120 --> 00:03:29,541
He told us to boycott the audition,
but he went there by himself now.

35
00:03:29,541 --> 00:03:31,375
I know!

36
00:03:31,375 --> 00:03:33,832
By the way, where are you going, Mini Min Hee?

37
00:03:33,832 --> 00:03:38,124
What? Me?

38
00:03:38,124 --> 00:03:39,832
What about you, Su Min?

39
00:03:39,832 --> 00:03:42,333
Me? I'm just...

40
00:03:42,333 --> 00:03:44,208
- Let's just go!
- Hurry, hurry!

41
00:03:44,208 --> 00:03:45,604
Let me go with you!

42
00:04:01,187 --> 00:04:05,667
Student from A wouldn't be here first,
so it must be a student from S.

43
00:04:05,667 --> 00:04:09,708
But I'm still relieved.
I guess they decided not to boycott anymore.

44
00:04:09,708 --> 00:04:11,754
Even so...

45
00:04:11,754 --> 00:04:14,416
they wouldn't get in with their level anyway.

46
00:04:14,416 --> 00:04:16,502
Why bother coming here?

47
00:04:41,160 --> 00:04:42,528
Yoo Il Lak

48
00:04:44,197 --> 00:04:45,831
It's Lak.

49
00:04:55,942 --> 00:04:59,445
But it was Yoo Jin Sunbae.

50
00:04:59,445 --> 00:05:04,183
When Milch abandoned us,
the first person who ran over to see us.

51
00:05:04,917 --> 00:05:08,487
When you showed up all drunk,
he gave you a violin lesson.

52
00:05:10,490 --> 00:05:13,192
The person who saved you
even if he told you he'd kick you out

53
00:05:13,192 --> 00:05:14,625
whenever you made mistakes,

54
00:05:14,625 --> 00:05:16,736
it was Sunbae.

55
00:05:16,736 --> 00:05:19,438
He wore the team uniform
for the performance, too.

56
00:05:22,768 --> 00:05:25,661
We thought we were the one
pouring everything on him.

57
00:05:25,661 --> 00:05:27,458
But it was not true.

58
00:05:27,458 --> 00:05:29,642
We received tons.

59
00:06:15,784 --> 00:06:17,500
What about the rest?

60
00:06:17,500 --> 00:06:19,859
Didn't you contact them
to come to the practice room?

61
00:06:19,859 --> 00:06:21,749
The rest of them won't go for the audition.

62
00:06:21,749 --> 00:06:23,496
What?

63
00:06:23,496 --> 00:06:25,164
The boycott is over!

64
00:06:25,164 --> 00:06:26,791
Yoo Il Lak went for the audition.

65
00:06:26,791 --> 00:06:31,471
To be honest, the ones who are not here
just needed the title of Han Eum Orchestra.

66
00:06:31,471 --> 00:06:33,583
Not everyone's goal was to become a soloist.

67
00:06:33,583 --> 00:06:35,291
I don't care.

68
00:06:35,291 --> 00:06:37,500
I'm going to put all my effort
into preparing to study abroad.

69
00:06:37,500 --> 00:06:40,413
I have enough performance experience.

70
00:06:40,413 --> 00:06:43,883
It hurts my pride to have an audition
along with the losers.

71
00:06:47,826 --> 00:06:49,166
Where are you going?

72
00:06:49,166 --> 00:06:52,291
I understand now
why Cha Yoo Jin and the dean dissolved ours too.

73
00:06:52,291 --> 00:06:54,041
A resume builder
and a step before studying abroad.

74
00:06:54,041 --> 00:06:55,876
Is that what it means to you?

75
00:06:55,876 --> 00:06:57,163
Don't be so upset.

76
00:06:57,163 --> 00:07:00,600
The real traitors are you, not Yoo Il Lak.

77
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:03,836
Is an orchestra some bus stop
to build experience before studying abroad?

78
00:07:05,538 --> 00:07:08,207
I'm going for the audition
even if it's just me.

79
00:07:08,207 --> 00:07:10,376
- Shi Won...
- What's with you?

80
00:07:11,978 --> 00:07:14,413
Orchestra is where you create sound together.

81
00:07:14,413 --> 00:07:17,283
If they had the least bit of affection
for the process,

82
00:07:17,283 --> 00:07:19,303
they couldn't say those things.

83
00:07:29,028 --> 00:07:30,930
Yoo Il Lak.

84
00:07:30,930 --> 00:07:32,364
Ma Su Min.

85
00:07:35,038 --> 00:07:37,698
That's the little one
who works part-time jobs all the time.

86
00:07:43,062 --> 00:07:45,431
They are definitely the losers from S...

87
00:07:46,341 --> 00:07:48,676
They are the losers...

88
00:07:51,050 --> 00:07:52,885
They've improved at a scary pace.

89
00:07:55,021 --> 00:07:58,024
Students of A are exceptional as soloists.

90
00:07:58,024 --> 00:08:02,161
But after two performances, their
skills have improved massively.

91
00:08:03,444 --> 00:08:05,333
It feels like a student
who ranked at the bottom

92
00:08:05,333 --> 00:08:07,080
placed in the top 10 of the class.

93
00:08:08,615 --> 00:08:12,916
Isn't this the first time
we get to pay careful attention

94
00:08:12,916 --> 00:08:15,041
to the individual students' performances?

95
00:08:15,041 --> 00:08:18,611
Yes, this is the first time.

96
00:08:20,846 --> 00:08:22,315
Is that Lee Jay Young?

97
00:08:22,315 --> 00:08:24,317
He's still good.

98
00:08:24,317 --> 00:08:29,588
But he follows his teacher's style
in bragging about his techniques.

99
00:08:30,189 --> 00:08:33,192
There is no improvement and no excitement.

100
00:08:33,889 --> 00:08:36,691
He'll continue to play the same way
for the rest of his life.

101
00:09:01,794 --> 00:09:04,262
What's gotten into you? You're a rude punk.

102
00:09:05,491 --> 00:09:10,791
Only half of A requested the audition.

103
00:09:10,791 --> 00:09:12,860
Was this your goal?

104
00:09:12,860 --> 00:09:16,697
To kick out the ones with too much pride
using the audition as an excuse?

105
00:09:22,236 --> 00:09:27,589
Using the audition as an excuse,
I hoped that...

106
00:09:29,210 --> 00:09:31,144
And see how much they've improved.

107
00:09:32,313 --> 00:09:34,916
The dean recommended you

108
00:09:34,916 --> 00:09:39,520
because you'd make fair judgments
if you listened to them.

109
00:09:41,999 --> 00:09:47,037
Professor Do is always against me,
but we have one thing in common.

110
00:09:47,705 --> 00:09:51,742
We express it differently,
but both of us care about the school.

111
00:09:52,676 --> 00:09:57,281
As much as you believe in your friends
I believe in Professor Do.

112
00:09:57,281 --> 00:10:00,317
So let's believe in him.

113
00:10:00,317 --> 00:10:06,323
He wouldn't make a joke
out of students' performances.

114
00:10:07,358 --> 00:10:13,197
- She said that?
- She said you'd be a fair judge.

115
00:10:44,228 --> 00:10:47,664
I'll announce the names
who passed the audition.

116
00:10:49,867 --> 00:10:52,035
List of New Orchestra Members

117
00:10:54,405 --> 00:10:56,073
Hurry, hurry!

118
00:10:57,241 --> 00:10:59,543
Excuse me!

119
00:11:01,412 --> 00:11:03,080
Excuse me!

120
00:11:16,541 --> 00:11:19,163
[Bass - Choi Min Hee]
There I am.

121
00:11:19,163 --> 00:11:21,999
- Me too!
- Me too!

122
00:11:22,733 --> 00:11:26,036
- Me too!
- I'm there, too!

123
00:11:27,304 --> 00:11:29,940
Yoo Il Lak

124
00:11:29,940 --> 00:11:31,575
There I am.

125
00:11:34,078 --> 00:11:36,613
All of us... made it?

126
00:11:38,882 --> 00:11:43,454
We are the members
of the best of the best orchestra?

127
00:11:43,454 --> 00:11:45,522
- Su Min!
- Min Hee!

128
00:11:48,826 --> 00:11:53,030
I believe that you will make it

129
00:11:53,030 --> 00:11:55,333
Like you said, I'm your conductor.

130
00:11:55,333 --> 00:11:58,569
I know about you better than anyone else.
And I'm saying that you'll make it.

131
00:12:00,738 --> 00:12:03,540
- We made it!
- Mini Min Hee...

132
00:12:06,434 --> 00:12:09,250
Il Lak, why are you crying on a happy day?

133
00:12:09,250 --> 00:12:10,881
Sunbae.

134
00:12:10,881 --> 00:12:13,817
We're not losers anymore.

135
00:12:13,817 --> 00:12:16,153
- Why are you crying over that?
- Stop crying.

136
00:12:16,153 --> 00:12:20,157
- Great job.
- You did well!

137
00:12:25,370 --> 00:12:26,709
I'm on top again.

138
00:12:26,709 --> 00:12:30,876
[Oboe Goo Sun Jae]
I'm not happy even if I got in.

139
00:12:30,876 --> 00:12:33,474
I should just be sloppy
before I leave to study abroad...

140
00:12:35,403 --> 00:12:36,375
What?

141
00:12:36,375 --> 00:12:39,334
[Trumpet Lee Jay Young]

142
00:12:39,334 --> 00:12:41,500
Why am I the second?

143
00:12:41,500 --> 00:12:44,542
A lot of our members are missing.

144
00:12:44,542 --> 00:12:47,017
But they are good.

145
00:12:47,017 --> 00:12:50,287
If they didn't make it today,
I'd have been disappointed in Professor Do.

146
00:12:53,157 --> 00:12:55,832
How could you bring the worst result ever!

147
00:12:55,832 --> 00:12:58,124
The ones who failed
are the children and relatives

148
00:12:58,124 --> 00:12:59,997
from the board and alumni.

149
00:13:00,798 --> 00:13:05,041
Even the students who got to join
the school finance failed.

150
00:13:05,041 --> 00:13:08,972
I'm sorry.
But I tried to be as fair as possible.

151
00:13:09,789 --> 00:13:14,000
Fair?
I thought you'd be different from Dean Song.

152
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:16,246
I'm disappointed in you, Professor Do!

153
00:13:18,548 --> 00:13:22,151
If their skills were at the bottom,
I wouldn't have given them the points.

154
00:13:22,853 --> 00:13:24,755
I am a professor.

155
00:13:24,755 --> 00:13:28,959
Above anything else,
I can't mess around with points.

156
00:13:30,533 --> 00:13:32,235
I'm sure.

157
00:13:40,304 --> 00:13:44,574
My title as a dean has crossed the water.

158
00:13:52,916 --> 00:13:55,452
I'm in the middle of class.
What are you doing?

159
00:13:56,186 --> 00:13:57,667
I'm taking a break.

160
00:13:57,667 --> 00:13:59,256
Don't bother me.

161
00:14:01,709 --> 00:14:04,918
[I'm taking a break.]

162
00:14:07,848 --> 00:14:10,317
Can I come over for dinner?

163
00:14:21,361 --> 00:14:22,796
Okay.

164
00:14:51,275 --> 00:14:53,210
Tell me.

165
00:14:53,893 --> 00:14:58,042
This time and the last time,
you did it for us.

166
00:14:58,042 --> 00:15:01,151
You didn't leave us because we're the losers.

167
00:15:02,277 --> 00:15:04,145
Then I'll believe you.

168
00:15:06,865 --> 00:15:08,499
I'm sorry.

169
00:15:10,494 --> 00:15:14,598
I should've believed in you guys
and stayed with you last time.

170
00:15:15,769 --> 00:15:18,268
I tried to resolve it on my own.

171
00:15:19,870 --> 00:15:22,339
"Arrogance with no luck."

172
00:15:23,140 --> 00:15:24,641
That was true.

173
00:15:26,710 --> 00:15:28,578
Cha Yoo Jin...

174
00:15:32,049 --> 00:15:36,334
Right, Cha Yoo Jin is a jerk!
He has no manners!

175
00:15:36,334 --> 00:15:38,375
He's full of things he doesn't have.

176
00:15:38,375 --> 00:15:41,558
But he does have loyalty.

177
00:15:46,445 --> 00:15:48,500
Let's not separate ever again.

178
00:15:48,500 --> 00:15:50,417
Should we make a token?

179
00:15:50,417 --> 00:15:51,635
Should we do a couple look?

180
00:15:52,493 --> 00:15:55,918
Or blood alliance like a real man!
Wouldn't it be cool?

181
00:15:55,918 --> 00:15:57,626
- I don't want to.
- Why not?

182
00:15:57,626 --> 00:15:59,743
Are you scared? I'll go first.

183
00:15:59,743 --> 00:16:01,945
Is there anything I can use to draw blood?

184
00:16:01,945 --> 00:16:03,814
Do you have a needle?

185
00:16:03,814 --> 00:16:06,283
Wait. Should we do this close to a hospital?

186
00:16:06,283 --> 00:16:10,087
What if I get it wrong,
bleed excessively and pass out?

187
00:16:10,087 --> 00:16:13,156
You do it alone in a place I'm not around.

188
00:16:13,156 --> 00:16:16,167
Why, what? I'll go first.
Hey, I said I'll go first!

189
00:16:16,167 --> 00:16:18,161
I'll do it!

190
00:16:28,772 --> 00:16:30,607
Thank you.

191
00:16:32,175 --> 00:16:34,277
Thank you, Yoo Jin.

192
00:16:41,285 --> 00:16:44,054
He told me to come over for dinner. Dinner.

193
00:16:44,922 --> 00:16:47,224
I'm leaving after dinner.

194
00:16:52,971 --> 00:16:56,107
My goodness, what do I do...

195
00:16:58,847 --> 00:17:00,816
He's not answering.

196
00:17:03,065 --> 00:17:07,703
Right, his door code changed.

197
00:17:09,613 --> 00:17:13,016
It was nice
when it was the same as my door code.

198
00:17:14,451 --> 00:17:18,688
We shared the same codes
as if we're a husband and a wife...

199
00:17:40,744 --> 00:17:42,312
Yoo Jin!

200
00:19:01,517 --> 00:19:04,686
I thought you threw them all out,
but you didn't.

201
00:19:05,407 --> 00:19:08,910
I didn't want
to bother separating garbage, so...

202
00:19:09,866 --> 00:19:11,267
Don't be shy.

203
00:19:11,959 --> 00:19:13,417
You just couldn't throw them away.

204
00:19:13,417 --> 00:19:14,738
Shy?

205
00:19:15,611 --> 00:19:18,180
You're just saying
whatever you want now.

206
00:19:19,825 --> 00:19:22,746
Yes, yes, I understand.

207
00:19:22,746 --> 00:19:26,383
By the way, I came for dinner
but there is nothing to eat.

208
00:19:26,383 --> 00:19:28,451
I bought dinner.

209
00:19:31,170 --> 00:19:33,500
I don't want instant food.

210
00:19:33,500 --> 00:19:36,751
- I'm the one providing food.
- Hurry up and make it for me.

211
00:19:36,751 --> 00:19:38,228
Let's order something.

212
00:19:41,578 --> 00:19:43,746
What's the occasion?

213
00:19:44,735 --> 00:19:47,270
So why in Korea?
Why are you looking for Yoo Jin?

214
00:19:48,183 --> 00:19:50,207
I guess Cha Dong Woo is getting old, too.

215
00:19:50,207 --> 00:19:52,409
Now you want to play your role as his father?

216
00:19:54,711 --> 00:19:56,209
Don't do that.

217
00:19:56,209 --> 00:20:00,417
Cha Dong Woo, you're like a plane
to our Yoo Jin.

218
00:20:00,417 --> 00:20:02,218
Bye.

219
00:20:03,820 --> 00:20:06,656
What's gotten into him, all of a sudden?
He's making me nervous.

220
00:20:15,265 --> 00:20:20,970
Father, I made it to the final round
of the junior competition this time.

221
00:20:21,772 --> 00:20:24,292
Everyone tells me
that I'll win the competition.

222
00:20:24,292 --> 00:20:26,142
If you come...

223
00:20:28,678 --> 00:20:31,709
- Of course you'll win that competition.
- What?

224
00:20:31,709 --> 00:20:34,918
I have no reason to go
unless it's the top performance on the top stage.

225
00:20:34,918 --> 00:20:36,553
Make that happen.

226
00:20:37,571 --> 00:20:39,373
If you want me to come.

227
00:20:40,824 --> 00:20:42,926
That's what makes you
the son of Cha Dong Woo.

228
00:21:03,637 --> 00:21:06,334
What's with the dream about Father
out of nowhere?

229
00:21:06,334 --> 00:21:08,718
It's been so long since we talked.

230
00:21:21,405 --> 00:21:23,867
- Tada!
- Tada!

231
00:21:23,867 --> 00:21:26,035
Rising star!

232
00:21:27,737 --> 00:21:29,172
Rising star?

233
00:21:29,172 --> 00:21:30,841
What do you think? Isn't it cool?

234
00:21:30,841 --> 00:21:32,943
We discussed all night to come up with it.

235
00:21:32,943 --> 00:21:34,744
I was against it, Yoo Jin.

236
00:21:34,744 --> 00:21:38,215
It's not old-fashioned! It's cool, isn't?

237
00:21:38,215 --> 00:21:39,883
Do we have to do this?

238
00:21:39,883 --> 00:21:42,719
Of course, it's the dream of all of us!
Rising star!

239
00:21:42,719 --> 00:21:44,254
Rising star!

240
00:21:44,254 --> 00:21:46,623
Leave me out of it.

241
00:21:48,758 --> 00:21:51,328
Isn't Almighty Cha the real rising star?

242
00:21:51,328 --> 00:21:53,864
You became famous!

243
00:21:53,864 --> 00:21:56,900
No, we can't decide on our own yet.

244
00:21:56,900 --> 00:21:59,769
We haven't gotten the approval
for the orchestra yet.

245
00:21:59,769 --> 00:22:01,972
Let's just decide on the music first.

246
00:22:01,972 --> 00:22:06,009
The dean said she'd schedule a date
for our first performance.

247
00:22:06,009 --> 00:22:08,845
I have a lesson soon.

248
00:22:08,845 --> 00:22:10,814
Can you finish in an hour?

249
00:22:10,814 --> 00:22:11,882
What are you talking about?

250
00:22:11,882 --> 00:22:15,185
We'll celebrate our foundation,
so let's go to my father's restaurant!

251
00:22:17,354 --> 00:22:18,989
Sorry.

252
00:22:18,989 --> 00:22:20,690
I have a lesson, too.

253
00:22:20,690 --> 00:22:22,993
We didn't go out as a group much.

254
00:22:22,993 --> 00:22:25,395
Do you think
we have a lot of free time like you do?

255
00:22:25,395 --> 00:22:27,530
Let's go together. It'll be fun!

256
00:22:32,269 --> 00:22:34,871
- Hurry up!
- I can walk on my own.

257
00:22:34,871 --> 00:22:38,741
It's been such a long time
since we all last ate at Mendelssohn.

258
00:22:39,876 --> 00:22:45,448
Lak made your lifetime free pass
for his father's dishes again.

259
00:22:46,816 --> 00:22:48,752
- Go, go!
- Nae Il, you're really...

260
00:22:48,752 --> 00:22:49,719
Hurry, hurry!

261
00:22:49,719 --> 00:22:52,856
Here comes Yoo Jin Sunbae,
the king of arrogant!

262
00:22:52,856 --> 00:22:55,558
Now, to your seat!

263
00:23:05,001 --> 00:23:07,270
I didn't know
this was Cha Yoo Jin's designated seat.

264
00:23:07,270 --> 00:23:08,738
Sorry.

265
00:23:08,738 --> 00:23:10,707
It doesn't matter who sits where.

266
00:23:11,675 --> 00:23:13,677
She's right! Just sit.

267
00:23:13,677 --> 00:23:16,713
Really? I'll just sit here then.

268
00:23:19,817 --> 00:23:21,749
I heard it's a party
to celebrate your return.

269
00:23:21,749 --> 00:23:23,291
Yes.

270
00:23:23,291 --> 00:23:25,555
But someone doesn't seem
to want to celebrate.

271
00:23:26,409 --> 00:23:28,277
Who?

272
00:23:31,928 --> 00:23:33,496
Where?

273
00:23:34,582 --> 00:23:38,041
Everyone's here to celebrate your return,
so stop making that face.

274
00:23:38,041 --> 00:23:39,448
You're talking very smooth.

275
00:23:40,103 --> 00:23:42,305
Thanks. How you speak is your character.

276
00:23:42,305 --> 00:23:45,075
You should also get used
to speaking in a nicer way.

277
00:23:45,075 --> 00:23:47,510
People around you will be more comfortable.

278
00:23:51,181 --> 00:23:53,283
Where is your father?
I should go say hello.

279
00:23:53,283 --> 00:23:54,951
He went out just now.

280
00:23:54,951 --> 00:23:57,287
He learns massage once a week.

281
00:23:57,287 --> 00:23:59,823
I see. You know about him very well.

282
00:23:59,823 --> 00:24:01,652
His father likes me.

283
00:24:01,652 --> 00:24:04,392
Oh, and I also received the lifetime free pass
for his dishes.

284
00:24:05,161 --> 00:24:06,763
I guess I didn't bring it.

285
00:24:06,763 --> 00:24:09,165
So anyone can receive it.

286
00:24:09,165 --> 00:24:11,500
Not anyone can get it.

287
00:24:11,500 --> 00:24:13,169
I haven't gotten one.

288
00:24:13,169 --> 00:24:16,873
Right, Lak?
You only gave it to two people, right?

289
00:24:16,873 --> 00:24:20,916
- Me, me...
- Yes, right! It's not for everyone!

290
00:24:20,916 --> 00:24:23,083
It's only given out to two people! Just two!

291
00:24:23,083 --> 00:24:28,832
To my best friend Cha Yoo Jin
and my very good friend Yoon Hoo.

292
00:24:28,832 --> 00:24:29,749
Just two.

293
00:24:29,749 --> 00:24:31,187
Just two?

294
00:24:31,187 --> 00:24:32,622
Thanks, Il Lak.

295
00:24:34,477 --> 00:24:37,301
Everyone's happy now that Cha Yoo Jin is here.

296
00:24:38,161 --> 00:24:40,897
I'm happy too. Let's get along now.

297
00:24:40,897 --> 00:24:43,124
- I'm leaving.
- Why? The food hasn't come out yet.

298
00:24:43,124 --> 00:24:44,749
Almighty Cha, do you have other plans?

299
00:24:44,749 --> 00:24:46,208
Have fun.

300
00:24:46,208 --> 00:24:49,832
If I'm going to decide on the music today,
I have no time for this.

301
00:24:49,832 --> 00:24:51,534
Bye.

302
00:24:51,534 --> 00:24:54,210
Let me go with you, Sunbae!
I'm leaving first.

303
00:24:54,210 --> 00:24:56,583
You're leaving too? Why? Hey!

304
00:24:56,583 --> 00:24:58,333
- I should get going too.
- What?

305
00:24:58,333 --> 00:25:01,217
- Have fun. See you tomorrow.
- You too? Hey!

306
00:25:01,217 --> 00:25:03,453
Lee Yoon Hoo! Hey!

307
00:25:09,159 --> 00:25:11,094
It's nice living in the same building.

308
00:25:11,094 --> 00:25:13,663
We can go home together like this.

309
00:25:13,663 --> 00:25:16,900
We don't need to go home together
just because we live in the same building.

310
00:25:16,900 --> 00:25:19,969
But it'll be odd to go home separately.

311
00:25:19,969 --> 00:25:22,906
We're not fond of each other,
so it could be better to go home separately.

312
00:25:22,906 --> 00:25:26,576
It's just you.
Yoon Hoo doesn't think that way.

313
00:25:27,744 --> 00:25:30,413
Hey, are you making fun of me now?

314
00:25:30,413 --> 00:25:32,749
I don't like Cha Yoo Jin much either.

315
00:25:34,951 --> 00:25:36,252
Yoon Hoo!

316
00:25:36,252 --> 00:25:39,989
Thanks. We don't like each other very much.

317
00:25:41,991 --> 00:25:44,227
See you tomorrow, Nae Il.

318
00:25:46,396 --> 00:25:48,431
Bye, Yoon Hoo.

319
00:26:26,903 --> 00:26:29,172
I thought I was almost there...

320
00:26:30,773 --> 00:26:32,642
but I'm back to where I started off.

321
00:26:36,045 --> 00:26:38,047
I'm so worn out.

322
00:26:47,757 --> 00:26:50,193
That melty butter boy...

323
00:26:50,193 --> 00:26:53,396
Don't be so mean to Yoon Hoo.

324
00:26:53,396 --> 00:26:56,499
He was so nice to us
when you weren't around.

325
00:26:57,167 --> 00:26:58,968
Your line is unclear.

326
00:27:00,003 --> 00:27:01,372
Make it clear.

327
00:27:01,372 --> 00:27:04,099
Whose side will you take
if I get into a fight with that butter boy?

328
00:27:08,178 --> 00:27:10,078
I take back what I just said. Forget it.

329
00:27:16,386 --> 00:27:18,187
I'll take your side.

330
00:27:24,063 --> 00:27:25,998
I mean it.

331
00:27:27,648 --> 00:27:30,500
- Really?
- Yes!

332
00:27:30,500 --> 00:27:32,735
I'm always on your side.

333
00:27:55,083 --> 00:27:57,458
It's Rachmaninoff.

334
00:27:57,458 --> 00:28:00,455
Is this the music for the next performance?

335
00:28:00,455 --> 00:28:02,157
It's not determined yet.

336
00:28:03,333 --> 00:28:09,005
I just wondered what it would feel like
if you played this music.

337
00:28:10,589 --> 00:28:12,625
Me?

338
00:28:12,625 --> 00:28:17,194
I think it'll be nice
to perform together later.

339
00:28:20,363 --> 00:28:23,599
If you get more serious about piano
than you are now...

340
00:28:24,415 --> 00:28:26,384
I guess it'll happen.

341
00:28:27,522 --> 00:28:29,855
Like a real couple,

342
00:28:29,855 --> 00:28:33,544
I'll be the pianist
and you'll be the conductor.

343
00:28:35,666 --> 00:28:37,334
Yeah.

344
00:28:50,661 --> 00:28:52,629
I'll get going now.

345
00:28:53,818 --> 00:28:55,699
It's getting late, and I'm getting sleepy.

346
00:28:55,699 --> 00:28:57,501
Okay.

347
00:28:58,962 --> 00:29:02,165
- Bye.
- Good night.

348
00:29:08,793 --> 00:29:11,529
She used to come at me before.

349
00:29:17,967 --> 00:29:19,535
Hello?

350
00:29:42,639 --> 00:29:46,813
Mi Na is not answering her phone again today.

351
00:29:46,813 --> 00:29:49,987
Maybe she thinks I ran away again...

352
00:29:51,057 --> 00:29:53,832
Did you even talk to her about me?

353
00:29:53,832 --> 00:29:56,693
Oh, I forgot.

354
00:29:57,340 --> 00:30:00,576
When I go back, I'll kill you first.

355
00:30:01,915 --> 00:30:03,999
Can you come back?

356
00:30:03,999 --> 00:30:06,208
The contract period as the conductor

357
00:30:06,208 --> 00:30:08,708
will be over soon.

358
00:30:08,708 --> 00:30:13,458
After that, I'll have to protect Mi Na.

359
00:30:13,458 --> 00:30:16,776
Who was it that put her
in trouble in the first place...

360
00:30:16,776 --> 00:30:19,583
- What did you say?
- No, no.

361
00:30:19,583 --> 00:30:22,152
Come back soon and earn points from the dean.

362
00:30:27,745 --> 00:30:32,083
This is Rachmaninoff.

363
00:30:32,083 --> 00:30:35,666
Is this the music
for the new orchestra's first performance?

364
00:30:36,545 --> 00:30:39,381
Did you find a pianist?

365
00:30:39,381 --> 00:30:42,259
No, I haven't decided on that yet.

366
00:30:42,259 --> 00:30:45,743
The orchestra hasn't gotten the approval
from the school yet.

367
00:30:45,743 --> 00:30:48,145
Go with this music.

368
00:30:48,979 --> 00:30:51,166
I'll present a pianist

369
00:30:51,166 --> 00:30:57,279
that the chairwoman can't
spit out or chew down.

370
00:31:13,083 --> 00:31:15,167
[Von Stresemann's the only apprentice,
Cha Dong Woo's son]

371
00:31:19,643 --> 00:31:21,812
We've arrived at Han Eum Academy of Music.

372
00:31:21,812 --> 00:31:23,980
Thank you.

373
00:31:27,084 --> 00:31:31,255
It won't be easy
for the members of A and S to perform together.

374
00:31:31,255 --> 00:31:34,291
Their thoughts and directions
are completely different.

375
00:31:35,726 --> 00:31:38,195
The relationship needs to be sorted out.

376
00:31:39,005 --> 00:31:39,958
That's true.

377
00:31:39,958 --> 00:31:42,522
[You Can Date Too]

378
00:31:42,522 --> 00:31:47,189
So I thought about our relationship...

379
00:31:47,189 --> 00:31:49,671
Weren't you talking
about the orchestra members?

380
00:31:50,774 --> 00:31:53,481
We've already passed
the first level, the green light,

381
00:31:53,481 --> 00:31:55,946
and the second level having a fling.

382
00:31:55,946 --> 00:31:59,314
What's left is the third level.

383
00:31:59,314 --> 00:32:00,851
Dating.

384
00:32:00,851 --> 00:32:04,254
Dating, dating, dating, dating...

385
00:32:06,034 --> 00:32:08,769
If you have time to read this,
look at the score.

386
00:32:09,955 --> 00:32:13,648
I borrowed it from the library.
Please pick it up for me.

387
00:32:13,648 --> 00:32:15,165
Hurry.

388
00:32:21,805 --> 00:32:24,439
I wondered
why you went to the library yesterday.

389
00:32:24,439 --> 00:32:26,189
This was it?

390
00:32:26,189 --> 00:32:28,979
This is a dating guide
that'll become my flesh and blood.

391
00:32:28,979 --> 00:32:33,250
- Let's do what this tells us to do.
- Do what?

392
00:32:35,719 --> 00:32:39,208
Seol Rae Im, then a heart shape next to it.

393
00:32:39,208 --> 00:32:42,459
[Seol Nae Il]

394
00:32:50,901 --> 00:32:53,648
Just Seol Rae Im. That's it.

395
00:32:53,648 --> 00:32:55,739
Seol Nae Il is too ordinary.

396
00:32:57,107 --> 00:33:00,610
Again. Seol Rae Im, and
a heart next to it.

397
00:33:02,846 --> 00:33:07,417
Seol Rae Im and a heart,
Seol Rae Im and a heart...

398
00:33:12,155 --> 00:33:14,958
Seol Rae Im and a heart...

399
00:33:16,126 --> 00:33:17,708
Seol Rae Im!

400
00:33:17,708 --> 00:33:18,832
That's the limit. I can't go any further.

401
00:33:18,832 --> 00:33:20,583
The important thing is the heart.

402
00:33:20,583 --> 00:33:23,874
Without the heart, it's the same
whether it's Nae Il or Seol Rae Im.

403
00:33:23,874 --> 00:33:27,637
Why is it the same?
It went from Nae Il to Seol Rae Im.

404
00:33:28,552 --> 00:33:30,721
You don't know
how to be thankful these days.

405
00:33:40,022 --> 00:33:41,723
What are you doing?

406
00:33:46,735 --> 00:33:49,333
And please give me a call twice a day.

407
00:33:49,333 --> 00:33:51,561
That's how you build affection.

408
00:33:54,164 --> 00:33:56,299
And I'm going to class.

409
00:34:04,494 --> 00:34:08,631
Nae Il, what is she so confident about?

410
00:34:39,832 --> 00:34:43,669
Son Soo Ji? The famous pianist?

411
00:34:45,524 --> 00:34:48,719
The board of directors won't recognize
the new orchestra.

412
00:34:48,719 --> 00:34:50,354
Chairwoman, the promise was...

413
00:34:50,354 --> 00:34:51,583
You created the problem

414
00:34:51,583 --> 00:34:55,458
by dissolving both orchestras
in the first place.

415
00:34:55,458 --> 00:35:00,625
No, S Orchestra was
the beginning of all problems.

416
00:35:00,625 --> 00:35:02,565
Von Stresemann...

417
00:35:03,318 --> 00:35:06,303
How could you bring such man...

418
00:35:06,303 --> 00:35:09,172
You'll have to take the whole responsibility.

419
00:35:18,882 --> 00:35:21,251
Who are you to barge in
without even knocking...

420
00:35:24,021 --> 00:35:28,158
You are... Miss Son Soo Ji!

421
00:35:30,661 --> 00:35:36,133
Which one of you
is the dean of Han Eum Academy of Music?

422
00:35:36,133 --> 00:35:39,469
Welcome! I'm the chairwoman of this school...

423
00:35:42,039 --> 00:35:44,240
Then you must be the dean.

424
00:35:48,779 --> 00:35:54,184
Hello. I came at the request
from Maestro von Stresemann.

425
00:35:58,755 --> 00:36:00,323
Von Stresemann?

426
00:36:00,323 --> 00:36:02,192
Franz?

427
00:36:02,192 --> 00:36:06,029
Where is he, by the way? Maestro?

428
00:36:08,899 --> 00:36:10,249
Please call him quickly.

429
00:36:10,249 --> 00:36:13,249
We'll just take a picture
of him and Miss Son Soo Ji.

430
00:36:13,249 --> 00:36:18,008
The meeting of a classical idol
and the world-famous virtuoso...

431
00:36:22,810 --> 00:36:26,379
So, I was fooled by Maestro?

432
00:36:27,437 --> 00:36:30,253
Miss Soo Ji, listen to me first.

433
00:36:30,253 --> 00:36:35,058
Did Han Eum plot this with Maestro
and fooled me?

434
00:36:35,859 --> 00:36:38,294
To make me come here and make me perform!

435
00:36:39,262 --> 00:36:42,132
- Plot together?
- If that's not the case...

436
00:36:42,132 --> 00:36:44,167
where is Maestro?

437
00:36:44,167 --> 00:36:47,170
Where is he? He's a professor at Han Eum.

438
00:36:48,839 --> 00:36:50,974
Did you make me come here alone...

439
00:36:51,675 --> 00:36:54,310
Did you send him to Europe
by any chance?

440
00:36:55,378 --> 00:36:58,215
Was Son Soo Ji tricked by Han Eum?

441
00:36:58,215 --> 00:37:00,550
Miss Soo Ji! Wait.

442
00:37:03,386 --> 00:37:08,691
I'll bring back
Professor von Stresemann right now.

443
00:37:29,346 --> 00:37:32,582
Indeed Mi Na's school is nice.

444
00:37:34,985 --> 00:37:40,423
Miss Son Soo Ji was supposed to arrive
at the airport at 11...

445
00:37:40,423 --> 00:37:44,194
so she should be at Han Eum by now.

446
00:37:48,965 --> 00:37:53,603
Mi Na! This is Franz.

447
00:37:54,337 --> 00:37:57,440
I just arrived. In front of the school...

448
00:38:02,779 --> 00:38:04,414
Mi Na...

449
00:38:22,365 --> 00:38:24,668
The tea tastes sweet.

450
00:38:24,668 --> 00:38:26,436
I should've done this a while ago.

451
00:38:27,971 --> 00:38:30,999
Son Soo Ji?
The world-famous pianist from Korea.

452
00:38:30,999 --> 00:38:32,876
The one who recorded
the complete work of Etudes by Chopin at seven

453
00:38:32,876 --> 00:38:34,166
and who performed at Carnegie Hall at ten?

454
00:38:34,166 --> 00:38:35,958
That Son Soo Ji?

455
00:38:35,958 --> 00:38:38,248
You know too many details
about Son Soo Ji.

456
00:38:38,248 --> 00:38:40,598
That's because, a long time ago, I was...

457
00:38:41,918 --> 00:38:45,791
No, my father was a fan of Son Soo Ji.

458
00:38:45,791 --> 00:38:49,208
That Son Soo Ji will really perform with us?

459
00:38:49,208 --> 00:38:53,163
Yes, with our Rising Star.

460
00:38:55,752 --> 00:38:58,101
We'll be upgraded to another level.

461
00:38:58,101 --> 00:39:01,304
Now I'm scared how far we can get.

462
00:39:02,598 --> 00:39:04,500
We can't be just happy.

463
00:39:04,500 --> 00:39:07,083
The media will flock here
because of Son Soo Ji.

464
00:39:07,083 --> 00:39:09,246
So we have to be completely ready.

465
00:39:09,246 --> 00:39:11,500
- Understood?
- Yes!

466
00:39:11,500 --> 00:39:13,517
I'm nervous.

467
00:39:20,724 --> 00:39:22,158
Seol Nae Il.

468
00:39:22,949 --> 00:39:25,458
Why aren't you coming to the lesson?

469
00:39:25,458 --> 00:39:27,297
Professor...

470
00:39:33,737 --> 00:39:36,667
No! I'm not taking your lessons.

471
00:39:36,667 --> 00:39:38,975
Stop! I'm not losing you today!

472
00:39:38,975 --> 00:39:42,278
Why are you doing this to me?
Don't follow me!

473
00:39:43,302 --> 00:39:46,405
Seol Nae Il! You'll flunk the class!

474
00:39:49,183 --> 00:39:51,807
She should come for just one lesson.

475
00:39:52,436 --> 00:39:54,738
She'll miss all the competitions this year.

476
00:40:02,780 --> 00:40:04,448
Yoon Hoo!

477
00:40:06,336 --> 00:40:09,091
Professor Do hasn't come here, has he?

478
00:40:09,091 --> 00:40:10,626
No.

479
00:40:15,645 --> 00:40:17,313
Persistent, persistent...

480
00:40:18,254 --> 00:40:22,325
I don't want to take lessons from him,
so why does he keep chasing me?

481
00:40:23,259 --> 00:40:25,327
It's because he's full of passion.

482
00:40:35,590 --> 00:40:36,991
Can you sign it for me?

483
00:40:38,316 --> 00:40:39,832
I'm going to request

484
00:40:39,832 --> 00:40:41,786
we perform our duet
at the Rising Star concert.

485
00:40:44,013 --> 00:40:46,482
Why the performance, all of a sudden?

486
00:40:47,617 --> 00:40:50,119
Let's just have fun and play as we've done.

487
00:40:51,748 --> 00:40:53,048
I don't want to.

488
00:40:55,618 --> 00:40:58,287
I want people to listen to our music.

489
00:40:59,211 --> 00:41:00,679
Our harmony.

490
00:41:01,984 --> 00:41:05,587
What sound we make,
what emotions we bring out...

491
00:41:07,094 --> 00:41:09,221
I want their applause.

492
00:41:09,221 --> 00:41:11,123
I don't want any applause.

493
00:41:13,403 --> 00:41:15,805
Just want to have fun like now...

494
00:41:15,805 --> 00:41:18,074
What's the meaning of music
without an audience?

495
00:41:21,845 --> 00:41:23,145
Sorry.

496
00:41:26,194 --> 00:41:31,083
That time, since I heard
you play Ravel's Water Game,

497
00:41:31,083 --> 00:41:33,474
I've always wanted to perform with you.

498
00:41:35,158 --> 00:41:38,628
I didn't want it to be just a practice.

499
00:41:39,929 --> 00:41:42,031
I wanted to be on stage with you.

500
00:42:12,228 --> 00:42:15,698
Mi Na, please let's talk.

501
00:42:18,802 --> 00:42:22,438
If it wasn't your request,
I wouldn't have put on a show like this.

502
00:42:23,940 --> 00:42:28,611
By the way, do I have
to perform with you, Maestro?

503
00:42:29,245 --> 00:42:34,183
Do you have another conductor in mind?

504
00:42:45,128 --> 00:42:47,697
Cha Yoo Jin.

505
00:42:47,697 --> 00:42:52,535
The son of the pianist Cha Dong Woo
and the apprentice of von Stresemann.

506
00:42:54,304 --> 00:42:56,439
I saw the performance on Youtube.

507
00:42:56,439 --> 00:43:01,544
I want to play my Rachmaninoff with this guy.

508
00:43:03,713 --> 00:43:08,351
This is called 'thought transference'

509
00:43:16,359 --> 00:43:18,428
It's been a while, Professor.

510
00:43:18,428 --> 00:43:22,198
Why is Mi Na still upset?

511
00:43:22,198 --> 00:43:24,834
Isn't it your trick?

512
00:43:24,834 --> 00:43:27,403
Nice to meet you. I'm Cha Yoo Jin.

513
00:43:28,037 --> 00:43:32,308
Straight and upright. The style I don't like.

514
00:43:33,009 --> 00:43:35,211
You're not a very nice style either.

515
00:43:37,213 --> 00:43:41,251
I think you two fit together.

516
00:43:41,251 --> 00:43:43,686
Work with each other and see how it goes.

517
00:43:45,088 --> 00:43:48,558
I don't have practice
with the orchestra members today.

518
00:43:49,314 --> 00:43:54,784
Then work the ears in the brain
with the ears that hear.

519
00:43:54,784 --> 00:43:57,017
I believe...

520
00:43:58,314 --> 00:44:02,057
you'll be able to imagine the orchestra sound
just with my piano sound.

521
00:44:45,048 --> 00:44:47,416
Rachmaninoff...

522
00:44:47,416 --> 00:44:50,500
This is the music that Yoo Jin suggested
that we perform together.

523
00:44:50,500 --> 00:44:56,541
It'll be nice to perform together later.

524
00:44:56,541 --> 00:45:00,363
When you get more serious about piano
than you are now...

525
00:45:01,537 --> 00:45:03,339
I guess it'll happen.

526
00:45:04,957 --> 00:45:07,259
That's my seat.

527
00:45:08,002 --> 00:45:10,304
That's the seat for Sunbae and me.

528
00:45:42,244 --> 00:45:49,151
Time nor Cha Yoo Jin will wait for you, Baby.

529
00:45:51,500 --> 00:45:52,541
[Request Form for Performance
with Han Eum Orchestra]

530
00:46:00,552 --> 00:46:02,333
Thank you.

531
00:46:02,333 --> 00:46:04,692
I'll work really hard
to make the best performance.

532
00:46:05,321 --> 00:46:07,689
I have to work hard.

533
00:46:08,476 --> 00:46:12,583
If I don't get nervous on stage,
I'll be able to do well.

534
00:46:12,583 --> 00:46:15,500
I got really nervous when I was little.

535
00:46:15,500 --> 00:46:20,349
A lot of time has passed...
I should be fine now.

536
00:46:20,349 --> 00:46:22,717
Of course! You're an adult now.

537
00:46:23,806 --> 00:46:26,909
Yes, I'm an adult now.

538
00:47:06,034 --> 00:47:08,249
Conductor.

539
00:47:08,249 --> 00:47:11,291
If we'll keep practicing individually,
I'll leave now.

540
00:47:11,291 --> 00:47:13,916
Yes, what's with this?

541
00:47:13,916 --> 00:47:17,022
It's just taking time
taking care of the losers.

542
00:47:17,022 --> 00:47:18,916
Hey!

543
00:47:18,916 --> 00:47:20,436
Are you saying that to us?

544
00:47:20,436 --> 00:47:23,239
Stop it. Jay Young, you should apologize.

545
00:47:23,239 --> 00:47:26,342
Am I wrong?
We have to prepare for competitions, too.

546
00:47:27,189 --> 00:47:30,206
I admit that Cha Yoo Jin has perfect pitch.

547
00:47:30,206 --> 00:47:33,416
But when he checks on every single thing,
when can we master the music?

548
00:47:33,416 --> 00:47:35,583
We've been doing fine so far.

549
00:47:35,583 --> 00:47:36,583
Yes!

550
00:47:36,583 --> 00:47:39,583
You're late all the time
and use your lessons as an excuse.

551
00:47:39,583 --> 00:47:42,152
Don't you know that it affected our practice?

552
00:47:42,892 --> 00:47:45,094
I really don't want to deal with the losers.

553
00:47:47,202 --> 00:47:48,669
Is that all you have to say?

554
00:47:51,267 --> 00:47:53,369
- Did I say something wrong?
- What?

555
00:48:03,800 --> 00:48:06,041
Let me know when the fight is over.

556
00:48:06,041 --> 00:48:08,417
We'll start the practice then.

557
00:48:09,037 --> 00:48:14,275
There will be no orchestra practice
before that.

558
00:48:17,427 --> 00:48:19,583
Let them do whatever they want.

559
00:48:19,583 --> 00:48:21,964
It'll be over if we don't approve anyway.

560
00:48:22,999 --> 00:48:26,035
Students from A are also there, right?

561
00:48:27,211 --> 00:48:29,839
Flowers in the greenhouse will learn
how scary the storm is

562
00:48:29,839 --> 00:48:32,007
when their greenhouses are gone.

563
00:48:35,981 --> 00:48:39,949
We'll make them come back
to Han Eum Orchestra.

564
00:48:40,683 --> 00:48:43,586
Concert? Says who?

565
00:48:45,040 --> 00:48:47,708
It looks like they'll go ahead with it.

566
00:48:47,708 --> 00:48:51,060
- If they become the official orchestra...
- That won't happen.

567
00:48:51,060 --> 00:48:52,708
Internally or externally.

568
00:48:52,708 --> 00:48:55,458
Problems are bound to happen.

569
00:48:55,458 --> 00:48:57,266
We'll wait until then.

570
00:48:58,907 --> 00:49:01,476
Until they fall down on their own.

571
00:49:05,364 --> 00:49:07,800
There is no support fund?

572
00:49:09,240 --> 00:49:10,916
I don't know what to say.

573
00:49:10,916 --> 00:49:14,917
There is no additional budget or fund
this year.

574
00:49:14,917 --> 00:49:18,625
Then what happens to our concert?

575
00:49:18,625 --> 00:49:20,022
Is it canceled?

576
00:49:23,110 --> 00:49:27,096
Why is it canceled?
Did we ever get any funds?

577
00:49:27,096 --> 00:49:29,398
That's right.
We can make it happen on our own.

578
00:49:29,398 --> 00:49:32,869
If it's really impossible,
we can hold a bazaar to fund it.

579
00:49:32,869 --> 00:49:36,205
That's great.
Then Il Lak, you can prepare the meal.

580
00:49:36,205 --> 00:49:38,774
You can prepare the costumes with Nae Il.

581
00:49:38,774 --> 00:49:40,509
- Okay?
- Okay.

582
00:49:42,109 --> 00:49:43,778
- Okay?
- Okay?

583
00:49:43,778 --> 00:49:45,380
- Okay.
- Okay.

584
00:49:47,683 --> 00:49:51,120
I can't be excused from the lecture?
The concert is ahead...

585
00:49:51,120 --> 00:49:53,189
It's not an official orchestra.

586
00:49:53,189 --> 00:49:54,500
You can perform,

587
00:49:54,500 --> 00:49:56,959
but you have to attend the lectures
and submit papers.

588
00:49:56,959 --> 00:49:59,528
And prepare for the practical test.

589
00:50:00,378 --> 00:50:04,482
Then I won't have time
to prepare for the concert.

590
00:50:06,335 --> 00:50:08,758
Why can't you?
Just do what you've done so far.

591
00:50:08,758 --> 00:50:11,107
Prepare along with the lectures?
And our practices?

592
00:50:11,107 --> 00:50:14,777
Were you excused from the lectures
when you had a performance?

593
00:50:14,777 --> 00:50:17,809
I didn't know about that.

594
00:50:17,809 --> 00:50:21,625
Right, I lost that privilege after leaving A.

595
00:50:21,625 --> 00:50:23,541
That sounds refreshing now.

596
00:50:23,541 --> 00:50:27,556
Right, just sleep during the lecture
and prepare for our concert.

597
00:50:29,325 --> 00:50:31,427
- Okay?
- Okay?

598
00:50:33,663 --> 00:50:34,964
- Okay.
- Okay.

599
00:50:57,893 --> 00:51:01,657
You're only focused on the score,
so you keep missing my notes.

600
00:51:01,657 --> 00:51:03,677
Pay more attention to my sound in this part.

601
00:51:05,484 --> 00:51:08,753
Yes. Sorry!

602
00:51:10,489 --> 00:51:15,063
Yoon Hoo, I think
we're practicing at a really fast pace.

603
00:51:15,063 --> 00:51:18,808
We may be able to master the music
way ahead of our performance.

604
00:51:18,808 --> 00:51:21,143
I can read the notes really well
these days...

605
00:51:21,777 --> 00:51:25,147
- Mi re do ti la sol fa so...
- Nae Il...

606
00:51:26,564 --> 00:51:29,625
Let's focus on practice
during our practice time.

607
00:51:29,625 --> 00:51:31,287
Yes.

608
00:51:40,262 --> 00:51:42,865
I think you're mean to someone else's puppy.

609
00:51:42,865 --> 00:51:45,301
Her ears are all down.

610
00:51:46,567 --> 00:51:48,268
Sunbae!

611
00:51:49,484 --> 00:51:51,791
- We're in the middle of practice.
- Do it tomorrow.

612
00:51:51,791 --> 00:51:55,678
- I made it clear that we're practicing.
- It's been four hours.

613
00:51:55,678 --> 00:51:57,999
I could only hear the piano sound
the whole time.

614
00:51:57,999 --> 00:52:00,333
Your cello sound was kept at minimum.

615
00:52:00,333 --> 00:52:04,019
You know
you're overworking Seol Nae Il's arms.

616
00:52:07,171 --> 00:52:09,292
Mind your manners to a girl.

617
00:52:17,390 --> 00:52:19,759
It's already been that long?

618
00:52:22,436 --> 00:52:24,337
My mind was rushing.

619
00:52:26,308 --> 00:52:27,676
What are you doing?

620
00:52:31,079 --> 00:52:33,219
Why do you just follow
what he tells you to do?

621
00:52:35,366 --> 00:52:37,134
But he's good at teaching.

622
00:52:39,121 --> 00:52:41,423
You were good at running away
when you were practicing with me.

623
00:52:41,423 --> 00:52:44,126
You told me to practice hard
the other time.

624
00:52:44,126 --> 00:52:47,129
I have to do that to play with you.

625
00:52:48,916 --> 00:52:51,585
So I'm going to practice hard.

626
00:52:52,425 --> 00:52:56,023
I won't wear a mask
and I'll dress nicely this time...

627
00:52:56,023 --> 00:52:58,259
I'm really going
to perform on stage this time.

628
00:53:01,517 --> 00:53:05,454
As long as I don't get nervous,
I can do well.

629
00:55:06,921 --> 00:55:10,558
It's okay. It'll be okay.

630
00:55:11,644 --> 00:55:13,999
It's not a competition.

631
00:55:13,999 --> 00:55:17,064
It's just a festival, so I can enjoy it.

632
00:55:25,139 --> 00:55:26,774
What do I do...

633
00:55:34,035 --> 00:55:35,335
Sunbae!

634
00:55:42,166 --> 00:55:44,369
You look happier today.

635
00:55:44,369 --> 00:55:45,403
You must feel confident.

636
00:55:45,403 --> 00:55:47,538
You're the one who looks...

637
00:55:51,208 --> 00:55:53,977
You look so amazing, I'm blinded by you.

638
00:55:53,977 --> 00:55:55,712
You're overflowing with confidence.

639
00:55:57,814 --> 00:56:00,717
I only need to show what I've prepared.

640
00:56:05,389 --> 00:56:07,090
Your hand.

641
00:56:13,096 --> 00:56:16,876
We'll be on the same stage today, right?

642
00:56:16,876 --> 00:56:19,303
Yes, although we'll be separated.

643
00:56:19,303 --> 00:56:23,440
Next time, we'll be able to go on together.

644
00:56:24,341 --> 00:56:27,708
If you do well today, it'll be possible.

645
00:56:27,708 --> 00:56:31,982
People will remember the name Seol Nae Il
in their heads.

646
00:56:35,773 --> 00:56:37,107
Let's go.

647
00:57:04,848 --> 00:57:06,483
Let's just get through today.

648
00:57:07,977 --> 00:57:09,959
Today...

649
00:57:10,846 --> 00:57:14,403
No, just half a day.

650
00:57:18,261 --> 00:57:20,397
It's only four hours.

651
00:57:28,916 --> 00:57:31,185
Nae Il, if you wear this and play the piano,

652
00:57:31,185 --> 00:57:33,554
you'll look like an idol
in the classical music.

653
00:57:35,386 --> 00:57:38,302
Son Soo Ji? Push her down.

654
00:57:38,302 --> 00:57:40,469
Push her down.

655
00:57:40,469 --> 00:57:44,231
Don't be nervous. Stay calm.
Just like any other day.

656
00:57:45,142 --> 00:57:48,402
- I'm getting nervous.
- You should keep it like other days.

657
00:57:48,402 --> 00:57:50,386
- Yoo Jin is conducting.
- Yes.

658
00:57:50,386 --> 00:57:52,773
I feel relieved just by that fact alone.

659
00:57:52,773 --> 00:57:53,808
Right?

660
00:57:53,808 --> 00:57:55,708
By the way, this is really pretty.

661
00:57:55,708 --> 00:57:58,541
- Will it really look Good on me?
- Is this like a couple ribbon?

662
00:57:58,541 --> 00:58:00,714
No.

663
00:58:00,714 --> 00:58:02,349
How long will you be chatting?

664
00:58:02,349 --> 00:58:04,418
Mini Min Hee, we need to go check
on the instruments.

665
00:58:04,418 --> 00:58:06,053
- Let's go.
- Go ahead.

666
00:58:06,053 --> 00:58:08,189
- Let's go!
- Let's go, Mini Min Hee!

667
00:58:08,189 --> 00:58:09,457
- You too, Su Min! You can do it!
- Let's go!

668
00:58:09,457 --> 00:58:11,792
- You can do it!
- Way to go!

669
00:58:26,046 --> 00:58:29,810
You're not nervous? I think I'm nervous.

670
00:58:29,810 --> 00:58:31,583
I know.

671
00:58:31,583 --> 00:58:34,048
I won't get nervous, so don't worry.

672
00:58:34,048 --> 00:58:38,052
You know today is very important.

673
00:58:38,052 --> 00:58:40,287
Sorry. I didn't mean to put pressure on you.

674
00:58:41,063 --> 00:58:43,666
My members practiced really hard.

675
00:58:44,334 --> 00:58:46,670
So believe in them and enjoy it.

676
00:58:47,965 --> 00:58:50,584
Our Rising Star will get approved

677
00:58:50,584 --> 00:58:54,125
as the school's official orchestra
with today's concert.

678
00:58:54,125 --> 00:58:55,518
Yes, I know.

679
00:58:55,518 --> 00:58:57,995
I'll keep my fingers crossed with your mother.

680
00:59:10,424 --> 00:59:14,465
We still have enough time,
so let's do a proper rehearsal.

681
00:59:14,465 --> 00:59:17,048
Of course.
There may not be practice in life...

682
00:59:17,048 --> 00:59:19,465
But there is a rehearsal in orchestra.

683
00:59:19,465 --> 00:59:21,152
That's right!

684
00:59:21,152 --> 00:59:23,755
Just as we practiced.

685
00:59:23,755 --> 00:59:25,323
We don't even need to do better.

686
00:59:25,323 --> 00:59:28,259
Almighty Cha, you look like
you're in a really good mood today.

687
00:59:28,259 --> 00:59:29,861
That makes me happy, too.

688
00:59:29,861 --> 00:59:33,007
Of course,
because I'm confident about my instrument.

689
00:59:33,007 --> 00:59:36,000
An orchestra is a conductor's instrument!
Is that right?

690
00:59:43,246 --> 00:59:44,918
He's in a really good mood today.

691
00:59:44,918 --> 00:59:46,465
I guess he trusts us completely.

692
00:59:46,465 --> 00:59:49,632
I know. I've never seen Yoo Jin that way.

693
00:59:49,632 --> 00:59:52,465
We can really be at ease today, right?

694
00:59:52,465 --> 00:59:54,549
To be honest, I was nervous.

695
00:59:54,549 --> 00:59:57,507
We have to do well this time
to get an approval from school.

696
00:59:57,507 --> 01:00:00,058
Don't make a mistake!
We just need to do well.

697
01:00:00,058 --> 01:00:03,094
We'll just trust and go with Yoo Jin's baton.

698
01:00:04,095 --> 01:00:05,563
Great!

699
01:00:22,113 --> 01:00:26,150
It's okay. It happened when I was little.

700
01:00:27,085 --> 01:00:29,153
I'm sure it's okay now.

701
01:00:32,680 --> 01:00:36,424
It's just a stage. I can just enjoy it.

702
01:00:36,424 --> 01:00:38,596
This is not a competition.

703
01:00:39,877 --> 01:00:41,756
All I have to do is enjoy.

704
01:00:41,756 --> 01:00:43,701
It's just a stage.

705
01:00:48,655 --> 01:00:50,340
You're here.

706
01:00:50,340 --> 01:00:51,965
Did you invite him?

707
01:00:51,965 --> 01:00:53,945
What do you mean? Who?

708
01:00:57,330 --> 01:00:58,683
Cha Dong Woo!

709
01:00:58,683 --> 01:01:02,053
He just arrived at the airport.
He's coming to see Yoo Jin's concert.

710
01:01:02,053 --> 01:01:03,627
Yoo Jin's father?

711
01:01:03,627 --> 01:01:05,726
My goodness...

712
01:01:05,726 --> 01:01:06,632
It wasn't me.

713
01:01:06,632 --> 01:01:09,060
I know about your relationship,
why would I have invited him?

714
01:01:09,060 --> 01:01:11,726
I know
the chairwoman sent an invitation every time

715
01:01:11,726 --> 01:01:13,788
but this time?

716
01:01:13,788 --> 01:01:16,756
Nothing will happen.
He'll just watch the concert.

717
01:01:16,756 --> 01:01:20,104
Cha Dong Woo started
Yoo Jin's phobias of planes and water.

718
01:01:20,104 --> 01:01:21,673
That perfectionist!

719
01:01:21,673 --> 01:01:24,842
What do you think he did
to that kid with his meticulous character?

720
01:01:24,842 --> 01:01:26,244
What?

721
01:01:26,931 --> 01:01:29,991
I don't know how much it'll mess up Yoo Jin
when he meets Cha Dong Woo.

722
01:01:32,016 --> 01:01:34,965
This can't happen.
I have to go and stop him.

723
01:01:34,965 --> 01:01:37,834
- Sun Young!
- Don't say anything to Yoo Jin.
